# Permission Rules

All access control must go through the permissions layer.

Never implement permission logic directly in routes or services.

Do not use checks like:

if (user.role === "admin")
if (document.ownerId === user.id)

Instead use permission functions:

canReadDocument
canWriteDocument
canDeleteDocument
canPublishDocument
canMergeDraftRequest
canWriteContext
canReadContext

## Scope hierarchy (drift-resistant)

Org scope decisions (view unit, scope lead, read owner context) live in **one module**:

`apps/backend/src/domains/organisation/permissions/scopeVisibility.ts`

Use:

- `canViewScope(prisma, userId, scopeRef)` – navigate / see org unit
- `isScopeLead(prisma, userId, scopeRef)` – drafts, trash tabs, lead features
- `canReadOwnerScope(user, userId, ownerInput)` – read contexts/documents by owner scope (sync)

Do **not** import `userAccessPredicates` in routes, services, or domain permissions except:

- `scopeVisibility.ts` (Layer 2)
- `assignmentPermissions.ts` (`canManage*` only)
- tests

Never add parallel `canViewTeam` / `getScopeLead` / inline `teamMemberships.some` hierarchy ladders.

Permissions must be centralized in:

`apps/backend/src/domains/*/permissions/`
